<p>
Let \(V\) be a vector space over a field \(\mathbf F\).
</p>
<p>
The <b>dual space</b> is
\[V^* := \Hom(V, \mathbf F).\]
Elements of the dual space are called <i>linear functionals</i>.
</p>
<p>
Related: <a knowl="facts/vec/dual">facts about the dual space</a>.
</p>
</body>
</html>
